2053:439.description:
⚠️ DEPRECATED - MARKDOWN: Detach when you need to add elements other than plain text in the blockquote.
A blockquote uses the “Blockquote/Border Left 3px $gray-100" effect in order to create the left border.
There's a “24px" space between the quoted element and the left border.

1924:410.name: Table (⚠️ DEPRECATED)
1924:410.description:
⚠️ DEPRECATED - MARKDOWN: Table (Starter table). By default the markdown table is striped. Each row has the options to turn on up to 10 columns.
To add more than 10 columns or rows, the table should be detached.

985:13.name: Code block (⚠️ DEPRECATED)
985:13.description:
⚠️ DEPRECATED Display a block of code. Commonly used for multi-line code and to display code with syntax highlighting.
Code blocks should fit the width of the parent container. Code content will scroll horizontally if it overflows the block.

Place this component inline with other text elements for your desired layout.

Both the player and the file are displayed regardless of browser.
The player should occupy the full width of its container, and the attachment link should be left aligned.
